article.headline: Tulsa 83, Prairie View A&M 54
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Rod Earls scored 13 points and Tulsa overcame an inefficient outside shooting performance to beat Prairie View A&M 83-54 on Saturday. The Golden Hurricane (8-1) had made just one of its first 18 3-point attempts when Calvin Walls hit one with 10:05 remaining to give Tulsa a 53-32 cushion. Tulsa compensated by outrebounding the Panthers (1-8) 46 to 25, forcing 24 turnovers and blocking five shots. Tulsa also shot 62 percent (23-for-37) when it stepped inside the arc. Walls and Charles Ramsdell had 10 points each for the Golden Hurricane. Jared Ellison had 12 points for Prairie View A&M, which has played all but one of its games on the road or in tournaments. The Golden Hurricane led 33-25 after a sluggish first half, then scored the first 12 points of the second half. Tulsa held A&M scoreless until a free throw by Derek Johnson with 13:36 remaining. The Panthers shot just 37 percent (17-of-46) for the game.
